contraindications.disease: Cases of life threatening hepatic failure have been reported in patients treated with nefazodone
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Nefazodone an antidepressant synthetically derived phenylpiperazine is used to treat major depression Although it is structurally similar to trazodone nefazodone has a mechanism of action different from other antidepressants and hence lacks the risk for major cardiovascular toxicity seen with tricyclics and insomnia and inhibition of REM sleep seen with the selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors
